1
00:00:10,910 --> 00:00:12,650
What was Qiao Zhenxing
doing on Zhongxing Road?

2
00:00:12,910 --> 00:00:14,220
We haven't found out yet.

3
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:15,700
Qiao Zhenxing

4
00:00:15,720 --> 00:00:18,260
drove to the
Forestry Bureau Reservoir alone

5
00:00:18,670 --> 00:00:20,210
and finished a whole bottle of baijiu.

6
00:00:21,160 --> 00:00:23,050
They said my brother
drank a whole bottle of baijiu.

7
00:00:23,830 --> 00:00:24,690
He didn't drink at all.

8
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:27,300
How could he go to the Yongqing River

9
00:00:27,480 --> 00:00:28,850
after drinking a bottle of baijiu?

10
00:00:31,600 --> 00:00:33,330
That whole area's been
under construction.

11
00:00:33,840 --> 00:00:35,770
The surveillance there
has been down for a long time.

12
00:00:36,520 --> 00:00:37,940
If there's no evidence,
we can investigate.

13
00:00:37,960 --> 00:00:38,690
We can verify it.

14
00:00:39,070 --> 00:00:39,820
If Sun Fei doesn't do it,

15
00:00:40,240 --> 00:00:41,730
we can take the case back

16
00:00:42,240 --> 00:00:43,540
and hand it over to the Municipal
Criminal Investigation Detachment.

17
00:00:43,880 --> 00:00:44,330
Worst case,

18
00:00:44,640 --> 00:00:45,500
hand it over to me.

19
00:00:45,710 --> 00:00:46,050
Right?

20
00:00:46,320 --> 00:00:47,330
I told you before.

21
00:00:47,350 --> 00:00:48,050
I asked you

22
00:00:48,070 --> 00:00:49,690
for his location records and call logs,

23
00:00:49,880 --> 00:00:51,650
but you made me stay out of it.

24
00:01:04,680 --> 00:01:05,130
Qin Feng.

25
00:01:06,120 --> 00:01:06,660
Still working?

26
00:01:07,560 --> 00:01:08,290
Come to my office now.

27
00:02:37,640 --> 00:02:41,840
[In the Name of Justice]

28
00:02:41,840 --> 00:02:44,840
[Episode 9]

29
00:02:56,030 --> 00:02:57,260
Use your head.

30
00:02:57,960 --> 00:02:59,660
If Wang Yu's problematic,

31
00:02:59,710 --> 00:03:02,850
this whole Wan Hai case falls apart.

32
00:03:02,870 --> 00:03:04,170
You should be clear on that by now.

33
00:03:07,840 --> 00:03:08,980
I'm really sorry,

34
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:09,780
Mr. Hong, and Mr. Li.

35
00:03:10,190 --> 00:03:11,610
Some of the department heads

36
00:03:11,710 --> 00:03:12,940
have other meetings to attend soon.

37
00:03:13,310 --> 00:03:13,660
Okay.

38
00:03:13,710 --> 00:03:14,730
Fine, I'll let him go.

39
00:03:15,310 --> 00:03:17,010
Li, you have my permission
to go to the meeting.

40
00:03:17,560 --> 00:03:18,290
Be good.

41
00:03:19,190 --> 00:03:19,820
Wait for me outside.

42
00:03:20,240 --> 00:03:20,890
Oh, okay.

43
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:29,380
Hong Liang.

44
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:32,690
This...

45
00:03:33,470 --> 00:03:34,780
This whole speech you just gave…

46
00:03:36,590 --> 00:03:38,130
you're not the only one thinking this way,

47
00:03:38,840 --> 00:03:39,170
right?

48
00:03:48,840 --> 00:03:51,340
Of the whole Guidance Group,

49
00:03:51,470 --> 00:03:53,780
I'm the actual brain.

50
00:03:55,630 --> 00:03:57,130
Team leader Zheng Yaping

51
00:03:57,280 --> 00:03:58,290
can't even compare with me.

52
00:03:58,310 --> 00:03:59,220
I'm telling you...

53
00:03:59,240 --> 00:04:00,690
Save it. You're the brain?

54
00:04:00,750 --> 00:04:02,260
Do you actually think you can fool me

55
00:04:02,280 --> 00:04:03,010
with that?

56
00:04:03,030 --> 00:04:04,100
We've known each other for years.

57
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:05,060
Why do you always have to insult me?

58
00:04:05,080 --> 00:04:06,100
Let me make this clear right now.

59
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:08,290
If your Guidance Group

60
00:04:08,430 --> 00:04:10,690
feels embarrassed
about returning empty-handed

61
00:04:10,710 --> 00:04:12,060
from Zhang Wenjing's case

62
00:04:12,430 --> 00:04:14,010
and wants to fixate on the Wan Hai case,

63
00:04:14,240 --> 00:04:14,980
fine, so be it.

64
00:04:15,240 --> 00:04:17,050
Take it up to the provincial office
and ask Prosecutor Zhang

65
00:04:17,240 --> 00:04:18,780
to send another Guidance Group.

66
00:04:19,040 --> 00:04:21,050
I will cooperate with them,

67
00:04:21,270 --> 00:04:22,900
just like I did with you
on the Zhang Wenjing case.

68
00:04:23,120 --> 00:04:23,580
Other than that,

69
00:04:24,240 --> 00:04:25,540
do not discuss the Wan Hai case
with me again.

70
00:04:25,720 --> 00:04:26,220
Understand?

71
00:04:26,240 --> 00:04:28,250
You idiot, do you really
not get what I'm saying?

72
00:04:28,830 --> 00:04:29,810
Which part of what I said was wrong?

73
00:04:30,240 --> 00:04:31,100
Think about it.

74
00:04:31,680 --> 00:04:34,140
If it wasn't just my idea,

75
00:04:35,070 --> 00:04:37,540
would we be having this private chat

76
00:04:37,560 --> 00:04:38,580
here in your office?

77
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:39,780
I would have

78
00:04:39,800 --> 00:04:41,610
taken you upstairs to meet with

79
00:04:41,630 --> 00:04:43,220
the whole Guidance Group.

80
00:04:43,480 --> 00:04:45,460
Why should I go up there
and talk to them?

81
00:04:45,600 --> 00:04:45,980
For God's sake.

82
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:46,730
Why should you? You don't know?

83
00:04:46,750 --> 00:04:47,610
The Group should come down.

84
00:04:47,630 --> 00:04:48,410
Don't you know exactly why?

85
00:04:48,430 --> 00:04:49,140
The Guidance Group

86
00:04:49,310 --> 00:04:51,220
is here to investigate
the Zhang Wenjing case.

87
00:04:51,240 --> 00:04:51,580
Yeah.

88
00:04:51,630 --> 00:04:52,850
But everything you just went on about...

89
00:04:52,870 --> 00:04:53,580
Zhang Wenjing was only

90
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:54,540
involved because of the Wan Hai case.

91
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:55,370
You listen to me now,

92
00:04:55,390 --> 00:04:55,980
you are not allowed

93
00:04:56,160 --> 00:04:57,930
to say another word
about the Wan Hai case.

94
00:04:58,070 --> 00:04:59,540
Can you stop doing

95
00:04:59,560 --> 00:05:01,290
useless, ridiculous nonsense?

96
00:05:02,600 --> 00:05:04,290
Here, my wife gave your wife some tea.

97
00:05:04,720 --> 00:05:05,370
Take it on your way out.

98
00:05:05,830 --> 00:05:06,490
Don't even wanna give it to you.

99
00:05:06,920 --> 00:05:08,290
Don't try to corrupt me

100
00:05:08,310 --> 00:05:10,250
with your little gifts all the time!

101
00:05:10,310 --> 00:05:11,490
I have professional integrity!

102
00:05:11,680 --> 00:05:12,610
I have a bottom line!

103
00:05:25,040 --> 00:05:26,290
Why hide this better one?

104
00:05:33,680 --> 00:05:34,100
Come in.

105
00:05:37,160 --> 00:05:37,610
Ms. Zheng,

106
00:05:38,160 --> 00:05:40,780
this is Wan Hai's defense lawyer,
Cheng Zijian.

107
00:05:42,310 --> 00:05:42,730
Please take a seat.

108
00:05:43,360 --> 00:05:43,700
Okay.

109
00:05:48,070 --> 00:05:48,660
Mr. Cheng,

110
00:05:49,070 --> 00:05:49,980
let me introduce,

111
00:05:50,390 --> 00:05:51,340
this is...

112
00:05:51,390 --> 00:05:52,170
Nice to meet you, Ms. Zheng.

113
00:05:54,390 --> 00:05:56,850
I met you before
at the commendation meeting

114
00:05:56,870 --> 00:05:58,250
of Haidong Provincial
Political and Legal System.

115
00:05:58,750 --> 00:05:59,810
You were on stage giving a speech.

116
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:00,980
We were all listening and learning.

117
00:06:01,070 --> 00:06:02,610
You're a nationally recognized
outstanding prosecutor,

118
00:06:03,040 --> 00:06:04,610
one of the top ten
law enforcement officers

119
00:06:04,630 --> 00:06:05,980
in Haidong Province.

120
00:06:06,510 --> 00:06:07,980
A role model for
many young people in our field.

121
00:06:09,480 --> 00:06:11,980
This must be Director Wang Chunxiang.

122
00:06:12,680 --> 00:06:13,980
Many of the cases you have worked on

123
00:06:14,190 --> 00:06:16,460
have been studied over and over
as model examples.

124
00:06:17,190 --> 00:06:18,340
You know us pretty well.

125
00:06:18,720 --> 00:06:19,410
To tell you the truth,

126
00:06:19,950 --> 00:06:20,780
I used to work

127
00:06:20,800 --> 00:06:21,850
in the political and legal system

128
00:06:21,870 --> 00:06:23,340
as a prosecutor.

129
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:25,340
So I know something about you two.

130
00:06:26,510 --> 00:06:28,100
But I'm not familiar with

131
00:06:28,360 --> 00:06:29,050
this young prosecutor.

132
00:06:29,750 --> 00:06:31,140
I'm Bai Ziyan, Assistant Prosecutor from

133
00:06:31,270 --> 00:06:33,220
First Procuratorial Division of Haidong
Provincial People's Procuratorate.

134
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:33,980
Nice to meet you.

135
00:06:34,360 --> 00:06:35,220
Then let's start.

136
00:06:37,120 --> 00:06:39,050
Ms. Zheng, if there's anything
you need to ask,

137
00:06:39,240 --> 00:06:39,850
go ahead.

138
00:06:40,160 --> 00:06:41,140
I'll tell you everything I know.

139
00:06:41,270 --> 00:06:41,700
Thank you.

140
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:46,930
Four days after Zhang Wenjing
was officially investigated,

141
00:06:47,430 --> 00:06:49,460
you took over Wan Hai's defense.

142
00:06:49,950 --> 00:06:51,850
And not long after, Wan Hai confessed.

143
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:53,810
We're curious,

144
00:06:54,190 --> 00:06:54,780
Mr. Cheng,

145
00:06:55,680 --> 00:06:57,100
how did you convince him

146
00:06:57,430 --> 00:06:58,490
to go from resisting

147
00:06:59,120 --> 00:07:00,250
to pleading guilty
and accepting punishment?

148
00:07:02,310 --> 00:07:03,140
Let me ask you,

149
00:07:05,190 --> 00:07:06,340
Am I a gangster?

150
00:07:07,430 --> 00:07:08,220
Are you not?

151
00:07:08,870 --> 00:07:09,610
Whether it is

152
00:07:10,510 --> 00:07:12,340
Provincial Procuratorate
or Municipal Procuratorate,

153
00:07:12,360 --> 00:07:13,370
they're on the same side.

154
00:07:13,920 --> 00:07:14,900
Now, you've been

155
00:07:14,920 --> 00:07:17,900
labeled as the leader
of a criminal organization.

156
00:07:18,070 --> 00:07:19,610
It's a done deal.

157
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:21,050
Don't get your hopes up.

158
00:07:21,310 --> 00:07:22,780
What hopes do I have?

159
00:07:23,510 --> 00:07:24,460
You know the best.

160
00:07:25,240 --> 00:07:27,780
I just want to serve my sentence earlier

161
00:07:27,800 --> 00:07:28,610
and go home.

162
00:07:34,830 --> 00:07:35,340
Mr. Wang,

163
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:38,020
when I took over the case,

164
00:07:38,360 --> 00:07:39,490
Wan Hai had already

165
00:07:39,510 --> 00:07:40,810
decided to plead guilty
and accept punishment.

166
00:07:43,830 --> 00:07:44,810
So that was a coincidence?

167
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:46,170
You can say that.

168
00:07:46,870 --> 00:07:47,900
But it does make sense.

169
00:07:48,480 --> 00:07:51,140
Imagine that, he's been sitting
in detention for over two years.

170
00:07:51,560 --> 00:07:53,580
His legal awareness
must have improved a lot.

171
00:07:53,920 --> 00:07:54,700
And he's come to terms with it.

172
00:07:55,040 --> 00:07:56,980
Plus, all that shady stuff
of his original lawyer

173
00:07:57,270 --> 00:07:59,100
got dug up by the prosecutors.

174
00:07:59,560 --> 00:08:01,140
There's no point in resisting.

175
00:08:03,950 --> 00:08:05,220
Did you know Wan Hai

176
00:08:05,600 --> 00:08:06,730
before he was arrested?

177
00:08:10,040 --> 00:08:10,490
No.

178
00:08:11,630 --> 00:08:14,580
Have you heard anything about him

179
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:16,290
or got to know him?

180
00:08:18,480 --> 00:08:19,610
We were total strangers,

181
00:08:20,270 --> 00:08:21,140
how could I get to know him?

182
00:08:23,800 --> 00:08:26,170
Mr. Cheng, do you have a bias

183
00:08:26,720 --> 00:08:27,370
against Wan Hai?

184
00:08:31,190 --> 00:08:31,660
Ms. Zheng,

185
00:08:32,440 --> 00:08:33,370
why did you ask that?

186
00:08:34,240 --> 00:08:34,850
You see,

187
00:08:35,360 --> 00:08:36,700
when Zhang Wenjing

188
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:38,610
was representing Wan Hai,

189
00:08:38,910 --> 00:08:40,220
she argued he was innocent.

190
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:42,340
But when you took over,

191
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:44,100
you went straight for a guilty plea.

192
00:08:44,670 --> 00:08:45,890
I want to know why.

193
00:08:59,440 --> 00:08:59,820
Understood.

194
00:09:01,790 --> 00:09:02,250
Ms. Zheng,

195
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:05,770
I made that decision based on
the chain of evidence

196
00:09:06,120 --> 00:09:06,940
presented by the case-handling organs.

197
00:09:07,720 --> 00:09:09,300
There is no doubt that
Wan Hai was involved in organized crime.

198
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:12,010
So I can only go with a guilty plea.

199
00:09:12,550 --> 00:09:14,300
I hope he'll plead guilty,
accept punishment,

200
00:09:14,670 --> 00:09:15,610
and get a lighter sentence.

201
00:09:43,720 --> 00:09:44,770
I gave him the tea.

202
00:09:45,840 --> 00:09:47,010
Pretty efficient.

203
00:09:47,440 --> 00:09:48,100
Good job.

204
00:09:49,550 --> 00:09:50,610
Son, time for dinner.

205
00:09:53,750 --> 00:09:55,010
What efficient?

206
00:09:55,960 --> 00:09:57,700
I didn't expect him
to be in my office today,

207
00:09:57,960 --> 00:09:58,610
sleeping.

208
00:09:59,270 --> 00:10:00,530
In your office?

209
00:10:01,120 --> 00:10:01,650
Sleeping?

210
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:06,130
Like a psycho.

211
00:10:06,480 --> 00:10:07,180
Got pretty aggressive

212
00:10:07,550 --> 00:10:08,460
and ended up arguing with me.

213
00:10:09,550 --> 00:10:09,940
What?

214
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:12,580
For what?

215
00:10:15,360 --> 00:10:16,580
I'm not gonna bore you with the details.

216
00:10:18,630 --> 00:10:19,250
The thing is,

217
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:22,060
Zhang Wenjing

218
00:10:22,870 --> 00:10:23,420
retracted her confession.

219
00:10:24,390 --> 00:10:26,010
That means
the Guidance Group's job is done.

220
00:10:26,120 --> 00:10:27,850
Shouldn't they pack up and leave?

221
00:10:29,360 --> 00:10:30,820
But they're not going anywhere.

222
00:10:31,550 --> 00:10:32,300
Instead,

223
00:10:33,630 --> 00:10:35,250
now their whole focus

224
00:10:35,630 --> 00:10:37,820
has shifted from
Zhang Wenjing to Wan Hai.

225
00:10:38,440 --> 00:10:38,850
Why?

226
00:10:41,390 --> 00:10:42,250
That's why you argued?

227
00:10:45,360 --> 00:10:45,700
I mean,

228
00:10:45,960 --> 00:10:47,700
aren't you two buddies?

229
00:10:48,150 --> 00:10:49,460
You two are so close.

230
00:10:50,030 --> 00:10:51,580
Didn't he give you any kind of hint?

231
00:10:52,320 --> 00:10:53,460
Hint?

232
00:10:53,550 --> 00:10:54,890
He practically spelled it out today.

233
00:10:55,510 --> 00:10:56,580
Actually, I know exactly

234
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:58,010
what he meant with every word he said.

235
00:10:58,240 --> 00:10:58,580
But,

236
00:11:00,240 --> 00:11:01,010
why was he doing this?

237
00:11:01,790 --> 00:11:02,940
If you ask me,

238
00:11:03,440 --> 00:11:04,820
you should go talk to him.

239
00:11:05,240 --> 00:11:07,060
He's the deputy leader
of the Guidance Group.

240
00:11:07,440 --> 00:11:09,100
If he knows anything,

241
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:11,300
he'll tell you.

242
00:11:14,320 --> 00:11:14,890
You eat first.

243
00:11:18,240 --> 00:11:20,340
Are you too embarrassed to ask?

244
00:11:32,670 --> 00:11:33,610
Eat some vegetables.

245
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:40,580
Hello?

246
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:42,300
Girl, it's me.

247
00:11:43,120 --> 00:11:44,700
It's been a while. How are you?

248
00:11:53,120 --> 00:11:56,200
[Boss: 6:30 PM, Room 806, Building 1,
Section 3, Dadu Xishan Residence]

249
00:11:58,150 --> 00:11:58,650
Huai'en?

250
00:12:00,910 --> 00:12:02,730
I gotta report to the 'boss' again.

251
00:12:03,960 --> 00:12:05,300
Need me to step out?

252
00:12:07,720 --> 00:12:08,250
Okay.

253
00:12:15,800 --> 00:12:18,480
[Boss]

254
00:12:23,550 --> 00:12:24,370
Good evening, boss.

255
00:12:25,790 --> 00:12:26,850
Appreciate your hard work, boss.

256
00:12:26,960 --> 00:12:27,700
Working late?

257
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:31,610
Got your message
about the time and place,

258
00:12:31,670 --> 00:12:33,130
but I don't know what it means.

259
00:12:33,480 --> 00:12:34,490
Li Yanxin's engagement party.

260
00:12:35,120 --> 00:12:36,180
Didn't Li Renjun tell you?

261
00:12:36,720 --> 00:12:37,370
Nope.

262
00:12:38,200 --> 00:12:40,420
I heard you two

263
00:12:40,440 --> 00:12:42,250
aren't on good terms because of Qiao.

264
00:12:43,120 --> 00:12:44,300
Who blabbed that?

265
00:12:45,480 --> 00:12:46,300
Who else could it be?

266
00:12:47,630 --> 00:12:48,220
Liu Yun?

267
00:12:49,080 --> 00:12:50,220
Don't tell me you're fine.

268
00:12:50,390 --> 00:12:52,300
She called me directly,

269
00:12:52,480 --> 00:12:54,530
saying I must come with you.

270
00:12:54,870 --> 00:12:55,610
I asked why.

271
00:12:56,120 --> 00:12:56,890
It's because

272
00:12:56,910 --> 00:12:58,420
he and his wife are just so petty.

273
00:12:58,750 --> 00:12:59,730
Okay, enough about this.

274
00:13:00,670 --> 00:13:01,420
Listen,

275
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:03,180
I'm sure I can't go.

276
00:13:03,390 --> 00:13:04,850
You go on behalf of us.

277
00:13:05,870 --> 00:13:06,370
Boss.

278
00:13:06,960 --> 00:13:08,370
Mind if I

279
00:13:08,840 --> 00:13:09,890
offer another solution?

280
00:13:09,960 --> 00:13:10,420
How about

281
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:12,420
you do me a favor

282
00:13:12,720 --> 00:13:14,420
